    "asOf": "2004-03-25",
    "date": "2004-05-17T20:19:06Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a deduction from gross income for unreimbursed medical care expenses and lost wages incurred in connection with the donation of one or more of all or part of a liver, lung, pancreas, kidney, intestine, or bone marrow to another human being for organ transplantation. Limits the amount of such deduction to $15,000 for each transplant procedure."
